        <updateDate>2006-11-28T17:35:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[Remarried Widows' and Widowers' Benefits Act of 2003 - Amends title II (Old Age, Survivors and Disability Insurance) (OASDI) of the Social Security Act (SSA) to allow remarried widows, widowers, and surviving divorced spouses to become or remain entitled to widow's or widower's insurance benefits if the prior marriage was for at least ten years.]]></text>
      </summary>
